fields.title: Introduction
fields.desc:
Prerequisites for following ahead

You probably will need some knowledge of HTML as it is required to learn the basics of JavaSript. The other things you need are IDE to make things easy along the road and a burning passion to learn and that is it.

I hope you are ready to learn and Good Luck
fields.conclusion:
once you feel like going ahead choose either to watch a long video that contains everything about this unit or watch it slowly with the chapters

 

Good Luck

fields.title: JavaScript Variables
fields.desc: Before jumping into any complicated codes you must first understand the basics of all programming languages and that is variables or simply a box that contains data. Don't be stressed you will understand it once you watch the video so good luck
fields.conclusion: I hope you understood the tutorial if you didn't I advise you not to jump to the next one and try to watch it again until you understand it. Don't be Afraid everyone started like you but if you understand it all press next and get to the next video.

fields.title: HTML understanding <body>
fields.desc:
A <body> is the part of the HTML that consists of everything visible to the user, so most of the time, this is where you will be working. the <body> element contains the <script> element at the end just before the closing tag(</body>) the reason for this is because all script tags need to be placed after the HTML and other resources.


<body>
.....
.........
<script src="link to some js file"></script>
</body>

 as you can see above that is one of the things you need to understand from this as it will save you from many headaches later on   there aren't more things you need to learn from this chapter as this is what you need to know

fields.title: Summary for HTML Basics
fields.desc:
What have you learned so far?

You've learned about the structure of HTML and its different components. You now know how to create a basic HTML webpage and understand what an IDE is and how to use it. You've also become familiar with attributes, tags, and elements, which are crucial concepts in HTML. You could say what is next, which is exploring more on creating content inside the body using the available tags in HTML, which will be explored in the next Unit.

 

Basic Structure of HTML

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

  <head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="description" content="Free tutorials for all">
  <meta name="keywords" content="learning HTML">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel='stylesheet' href='location to css file'>

  </head>

    <body>
 ..........
.......
<script src="location to js file "></script>
    </body>

</html>

 This is the basic structure of HTML you learned in the first chapter with the meta tags you learned in the fifth tutorial as well as the things you learned in the sixth chapter. this code above summarizes everything you have learned until now. 

 

So it has been pretty easy until now right you may even think this is too easy but wait don't jump off the horse yet. because everything is easy when you start it but becomes hard as you progress, so the advice I am giving is Don't give up 

 

Once you are ready Continue To the Next Unit

fields.title: Exercise for the Basics of HTML
fields.desc:
So now you have finished your first Unit it is time to test yourself right. 

 

What is the Exercise?

It is going to be a simple exercise where you create an HTML file that will consist of the Basics of HTML as well as certain elements. so what do you need for this exercise?

  1. You need to create an HTML file with a name index.
  2. You need to write the basic structure of HTML inside it.
  3. You then add meta tags at the head of the HTML.
  4. Create a title with your name.

If you want to try it here here is a simple code editor for you

fields.title: JavaScript DataType
fields.desc:
DataType is what you call the nationality of the data you are working on according to this nationality a computer system will process and analyze the data differently.

An example is when you write a number and a word according to what you write the computer interprets it differently if it is a number you can add and subtract and if it is a word you can split it into alphabets but you cannot add or subtract words similarly you cant spilt numbers. that is what datatype is about there are more than two data types and you will understand more of them later.
